examples.en: Don't leave your valuables in plain sight.
He gave me valuable information.
She is a valuable member of the staff.
I learned a valuable lesson.
The watch is extremely valuable.
The bank provides safe custody for valuables.
The thieves stripped the house of its valuables.
You should store your valuables in a secure place.
If you leave valuables in your car it will tempt thieves.
It's valuable to know languages if you work in an export firm.
Clean air is a valuable natural resource that needs to be protected.
Gold, during the Middle Ages, was about sixteen times more valuable than the same weight of silver.
A lot of valuable advice can be found in this book.
Please don't waste my time. My time is very valuable.
Guests should leave their valuables in the hotel safe.
The volunteers provide a valuable service to the community.
He made many valuable contributions to the field of science.
A safe is provided to keep your valuables secure from potential thieves.
The hotel recommended that we keep all our valuables in its safe during our stay.
The theft of the jewelry and other valuables was immediately reported to the police.
